Yogurt Cake with Fresh Berries
  --Sur la Table

2 c unbleached ap flour + 1 tbsp for dusting raspberries
1 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp fine sea salt
1 c  sugar
1 large lemon, zested
1 c 2% or whole-fat Greek yogurt
1 c vegetable oil + extra for greasing pan
2 large eggs
1 tsp vanilla bean paste
2 c fresh raspberries, divided
confectioners’ sugar, for dusting

Preheat oven to 350F. Grease an 8x4" loaf pan. To a medium bowl, add 2 c flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt; whisk together and set aside. To a separate medium bowl, add the sugar, zest, yogurt, oil, eggs, and vanilla bean paste; whisk until smooth and well combined. Add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture; stir just until combined. Toss 1 c of raspberries with 1 tbsp of flour and gently fold into the cake batter. Spread the batter evenly in the prepared loaf pan or muffin tray. Bake for 65-70 min for the loaf, or until cakes are firm to the touch but still very moist in the center. Cool on a wire rack. Dust cake with confectioners’ sugar and serve with remaining raspberries.
